    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation level for model risk level 3. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved 1 vs. required 2) is acknowledged and documented; the multi-laboratory experimental design and the quantitative E/uval metric passing across all QoIs provide sufficient compensating evidence to support an overall Accepted determination at Medium assurance level. Uncertainty quantification was performed across material and geometric input distributions; the UQ technical report narrative references a screening sensitivity study that identified elastic modulus and rod diameter as dominant variance contributors. The FEA ensemble framework is credible for the stated COU.",
